premise_source_doc_sentence: Christopher Crosby Farley  (  February 15 , 1964 -- December 18 , 1997  )  was an American actor and comedian .

Farley was known for his loud , energetic comedic style , and was a member of Chicago 's Second City Theatre and later a cast member of the NBC sketch comedy show Saturday Night Live between 1990 and 1995 .
Farley died of a drug overdose in 1997 at the age of 33 .

Farley died of cancer in October 1989 , shortly before the publication of The Young Black Stallion , the twenty-first book in the Black Stallion series and after the start of production on the television series The Adventures of the Black Stallion .
Similar to his idol , John Belushi , Farley died of a speedball overdose at the age of 33 .
After Farley died in 1997 before he could finish , Mike Myers was brought in to work for the character , who after his first recording decided to record his voice in a Scottish accent .
The documentary is based on the life of comedian actor Chris Farley and features interviews with numerous actors , comedians and others who worked with Farley during his career .
Shrek originally cast Chris Farley to do the voice for the title character , recording about 80 % -- 90 % of his dialogue .
